<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 27 at 11:25AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT THROUGH 8 PM...
A wintry mix of snow, sleet and freezing rain will expand across
the area during the afternoon hours. Potential exists for bursts
of heavier snow and sleet, leading to a rapid accumulation on area
roadways. In addition, a glaze of ice will be possible on
untreated roadways, bridges, exit ramps, overpasses, and other
untreated surfaces. Visibility may drop below 1 mile at times
during the heaviest periods of precipitation. Motorists should
remain aware of possible changes in driving conditions and allow
for extra time when traveling this afternoon.</description>
